name: AT HOME AT 322 EAST 57TH STREET
description: About AT HOME AT 322 EAST 57TH STREET Brilliant light pours into this unique six room duplex located at 322 East 57th street. The building is among the very few in NYC with double height living rooms. Built in 1929 the apartments were originally designed as artists' studios. This elegant apartment is located on a high floor and has open and unobstructed views of the skyline. An oak-paneled library overlooks the double height living room, adding to the drama of this distinctive apartment. Upon entering the lower level, one finds the entertaining rooms. White Carrara marble floors flow throughout the gallery, formal dining room and double height drawing room. All of the entertaining rooms are covered in 18th century, Louis 15th boiserie. A modern chef's kitchen is adjacent to the formal dining room. On the upper level one enters the oak paneled library/media room. Two bedrooms, two and half baths and a laundry room complete the upper level. The expansive, master bedroom receives continuous light all day long from south and east exposures. A wood burning marble fireplace adds a cozy effect. The second bedroom, also, enjoys double exposures to the south and west. Known as home to prominent literary figures, designers, architects and artists, 322 East 57th street was reputed to be the home of Orson Wells. Luminaries who have lived in the building include Clay Felker, founder of New York Magazine and his wife, author Gail Sheehy, Tamara de Lempicka, the famous painter of the Art Deco period, Lilly Ponds, famous coloratura and Andre Kostelanetz, her conductor husband, John Fleming, one of the great book collectors of the 20th century. Built in 1929, the original apartments were designed without kitchens, as it was customary to dine in the restaurant on the first floor. Today, that restaurant is Mr. Chows and Michael and Tina Chow lived in the building. Photos courtesy of Mike Tauber & Billy Cunningham AT HOME AT 322 EAST 57TH STREET is a townhouse located in Manhattan County, the 10022 ZIP Code, and the Nyc Geog District # 2 - Manhattan attendance zone.
address: 322 E 57th St, New York, NY 10022  Hell's Kitchen

name: The Ecoliving House at 424 W 47th St
description: About The Ecoliving House at 424 W 47th St As of 4/23/2021, we have been under new management! The Ecoliving House at 424 West 47th offers the only sustainable co-living experience in the heart of Manhattan. What is co-living? It's a shared housing community where members have their own private bedrooms and share kitchens, living rooms, and other common spaces with other members. Pricing for private bedrooms is all inclusive of furniture, utilities, wifi, laundry, 2x a week cleaning, basic supplies, and community events. Flexible lease lengths are allowed (minimum 1 month), with discounts at 1 year leases. There are three apartment layouts in the building. Below are links to 3D tours: 1R: https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=ask9vYdT2C5 2nd-5th floor R: https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=X4EMSHiDX78 2nd-5th floor F: https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=UYGGKU3eEEk Lobby: https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=EpS4SvLEzx3 Roof Deck: https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=bwExW8tAr5Z Please refer to listing details for more information on individual apartments, or call our live-in manager, Roddy, to schedule a video or in-person tour. Apartment finishes: The bedrooms are furnished with a bed, nightstand, two sets of ceiling lights, and a ceiling fan. The kitchens are appointed with high-end cabinets imported from Germany, Dekton countertops, induction cooktops, and theyâre fully stocked with dishware, cooking tools, appliances, and other essentials. Many of the bedrooms have private en-suite bathrooms. All bathrooms are equipped with Bio-bidet heated smart toilet seats and low-flow High Sierra showerheads. Building Amenities: On the ground floor, a tastefully designed common lounge is accessible to all members, highlighted by a Mondrian-inspired sequin wall in the lobby. Storage cages and bike racks are available in the cellar, and a gym is coming soon! Crowning the building is a stunning Shigeo Kawasaki-designed green roof with a front-row seat to the midtown skyline. A Sustainable Community: There is a plethora of eco-friendly hardware in the building. The green roof features a 40-panel, 14.4 kW solar canopy (one of only a few in Manhattan). Motion sensor lights have been installed strategically throughout the building, mirror arrays redirect sunlight to the lower floors, and low-flow showerheads and toilets are in every bathroom. But the heart of The Ecoliving House is our community. And every member is encouraged to adopt sustainable practices outlined at move-in, like participating in our composting and gardening program on the roof. Furthermore, we regularly host community events where you can meet other members throughout the building so you can build relationships that last beyond your stay with us. Neighborhood: The Ecoliving House is ideally situated between restaurant row, Broadway, Times Square, and the scenic Hudson River Park. The A/C/E/1/N/R/W and Port Authority are within a 10-minute walk, and a Citibike station is on the corner of 47th and 10th. The Ecoliving House at 424 W 47th St is an apartment located in Manhattan County, the 10036 ZIP Code, and the Nyc Geog District # 2 - Manhattan attendance zone. description: About 130 E 62nd St New York, NY 10065 We specialize in furnished short term rental apartments, extended-stay & corporate housing accommodations in the heart of New York City on the Upper East Side of Manhattan. As the brownstone was built in 1871, it is not handicap accessible. All apartments are accessed via our central open staircase. There isn't an elevator. We regret we are unable to accommodate pets (sorry, no exceptions). Smoking is not permitted. All stays must meet our 30-90 day min. Annual leases welcome. Tucked among gorgeous townhouses and other historic buildings between Park and Lexington Avenues, the Brownstone offers charming accommodations a couple of blocks from Central Park, Madison Avenue shopping and Manhattan's finest restaurants and cafes. The generously sized apartment-style suites are housed within a 5-story classic 1870's era brownstone on an inviting residential street. The historic turn-of-the-century brownstone townhouse brings style and quaintness to the busy city. Views of beautiful East 62nd Street Mansions or serene garden views. The wonderful stylized apartments of the townhouse offer antique furniture, hardwood floors, beautiful beds, en suite private bathrooms, as well as high ceilings, marble fireplace mantels and modern amenities such as flat-screen TVs and Wi-Fi. Some rooms offer a kitchen or kitchenette and separate dining areas. Set on a tree-lined street, the beautiful brownstone building is situated in the much sought after LENOX HILL neighborhood of the Historic Upper East Side section of Manhattan and a 5-minute walk to CENTRAL PARK. Bloomingdales is 2 blocks away. The house is just 3 blocks from bustling Midtown Manhattan. Some of the City's fabulous and world renown Museums & galleries including the Metropolitan Museum of Art, MoMA and the Frick Museum are close by.
